s.","fix":"Correct birth certificates linking applicant to sponsor","severity":"Medium"}],"faqs":[{"q":"Can we guarantee Super Visa approval?","a":"No. IRCC assesses medical, insurance, LICO, and ties. Never promise approval."},{"q":"How much income sponsor needs?","a":"Verify current LICO table on canada.ca for family size including sponsoring household."},{"q":"Which insurance companies?","a":"Must be Canadian company offering Super Visa compliant coverage—verify with insurer."},{"q":"Difference from regular TRV?","a":"Super Visa allows up to 5-year stays per entry; higher LICO and insurance requirements."},{"q":"Can both parents apply together?","a":"Yes; assess combined documentation and sponsor income for family size."},{"q":"Medical exam when?","a":"Before application; use IRCC panel physician."},{"q":"Processing time from India?","a":"Often 3–8 months—check current IRCC processing times."},{"q":"Can Super Visa holder work?","a":"No. Visit and family time only—not employment."},{"q":"What is Description for this service?","a":"Multi-entry visa allowing parents and grandparents of Canadian citizens/PRs to visit for up to 5 years per entry without renewing status."},{"q":"What is Eligible applicants for this service?","a":"Parent/grandparent of Canadian citizen or PR · Child/grandchild meets LICO income threshold · Medical exam · Canadian medical insurance · Ties to home country"},{"q":"What is Insurance requirement for this service?","a":"Private medical insurance from Canadian company valid minimum 1 year from entry, $100,000 minimum coverage."},{"q":"Important note on Insurance requirement?","a":"Private medical insurance from Canadian company valid minimum 1 year from entry, $100,000 minimum coverage."},{"q":"What is Key authority for this service?","a":"Immigration, Refugees and Citizenship Canada (IRCC)"},{"q":"What is After approval for this service?","a":"Multi-entry visa; maintain valid insurance on each visit; respect super visa conditions."},{"q":"Is 